news.title: Slum dwellers rush to Gujarat HC over Ahmedabad civic body's demolition bid
news.para: The AMC filed an application on July 7 and urged the HC for an early hearing on the petition filed by the slum dwellers, who have been demanding alternative accommodation if the civic body and government want to implement TP Scheme No. 5 (City Wall Improvement) Section-3.

news.title: Goa: SIT says real land owners not claiming properties
news.para: The SIT itself has registered 12 first information reports (FIRs) pertaining to land-grab, while 28 FIRs were transferred to it.

news.title: Society redevelopment law challenged in Gujarat HC
news.para: Questioning the validity of the rules, Petitioner Pragnesh Gandhi, a resident of Naranpura, stated that the authorities grant permission for redevelopment only if they have the consent of 75% of members, and that too only if the building is at least 25 years old.
